## Sidebar Navigation

The sidebar navigation has specific behavior based on screen size:
- Desktop: Always visible (expanded)
- Mobile: Hidden by default, shown when toggled

Implementation in [src/components/SuperAdmin/Layout/Sidebar/index.tsx](mdc:src/components/SuperAdmin/Layout/Sidebar/index.tsx)

## Tailwind Responsive Classes

Use Tailwind's responsive prefixes consistently:
- `sm:` (640px and up)
- `md:` (768px and up)
- `lg:` (1024px and up)
- `xl:` (1280px and up)
- `2xl:` (1536px and up)

Example:
```tsx
<div className="p-2 md:p-4 lg:p-6">
  {/* Content that has different padding at different breakpoints */}
</div>
```

## Images and Assets

Ensure images and assets are optimized for different screen sizes:
- Use responsive image techniques
- Consider different image sizes for different breakpoints
- Optimize assets for mobile data usage

